n^2\beta_n \to 0
 n \to \infty
c_{n+1} = \frac{1}{n}\sum\limits_{i=1}^n i\beta_{i}
c_n
n\beta_n\rightarrow 0
i\beta_i
n c_{n+1} = (n-1) c_n +  \gamma_n
\gamma_n = n \beta_n
n \gamma_n \to 0
c_n = \frac{1}{n-1}\sum_{j=1}^{n-1} a_j 
\sum_{j=1}^{n} a_j = \sum_{j=1}^{n-1} a_j +\gamma_n \implies a_n=\gamma_n
